Snapwood Apps, LLC (“we,” “us,” or “our”) respects the privacy of its users (“you” or “your”). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our Android, Amazon, and iOS apps (the “Application”) on your device. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not access the Application.
The Application is designed to allow you to access, display, and manage your photos stored in Google Drive, Google Photos, Dropbox, OneDrive, or Flickr (“Cloud Services”) on your device. We are committed to protecting your privacy and handling your data in an open and transparent manner.
Information We Collect
The Application accesses your Cloud Services, such as Google Drive, data solely for the purpose of displaying your photos and photo slideshows on your device. We do not collect or store any personal information about you.
How We Use Your Information
The Application uses the information accessed from Cloud Services, such as Google Drive, to:
Display and manage photos and photo slideshows on your device.
Cache photos locally on your device to improve app performance.
Data Storage and Security
Photos accessed by the Application may be cached locally on your device to enhance performance. These cached data remain on your device and are not transferred to any external servers or third parties.
All data transfer with Cloud Services are protected by HTTPS encryption.  Your sensitive data, such as authorization keys, are encrypted to secure data access and remain on your device.  These authorization keys can be revoked by you at any time through the Cloud Services’ website.
Data Retention and Deletion
Cached data on your device are retained only to facilitate the Application’s performance and user experience. You may clear the cached data through the Application settings or by uninstalling the Application. Upon uninstallation, all locally stored data will be deleted from your device.
Data Sharing and Transfer
We do not share or transfer your data to third parties. The Application does not allow any third party to access your Cloud Services, such as Google Drive, data. Your data remains confidential and is used solely for the purpose of providing the services offered by the Application.
Your Rights
You have the right to access and control your data. The Application uses Google’s APIs to access your Google Drive data, and such use is subject to Google’s Privacy Policy and Terms of Service.  You may revoke access to the Application at any time by revoking app access on the Cloud Services website.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
Contact Us
If you have any questions or suggestions about our Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contact us at help@snapwoodapps.com.